messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the implementation of App\Http\Controllers\Admin\CommentController:

- app/Http/Controllers/Admin/CommentController.php

Explanation:
- routes/admin.php registers a resource route for "comments" pointing to App\Http\Controllers\Admin\CommentController, limited to index, edit, update and destroy.
- The implementation lives in app/Http/Controllers/Admin/CommentController.php. That file defines the four handlers used by the route:
  - index(): returns the admin.comments.index view with paginated comments (with post and author relations).
  - edit(Comment $comment): returns the admin.comments.edit view with the comment and a users list.
  - update(CommentsRequest $request, Comment $comment): validates via App\Http\Requests\Admin\CommentsRequest, updates the comment, then redirects back to the edit route with a success message.
  - destroy(Comment $comment): deletes the comment and redirects to the comments index with a success message.
- The request class referenced is app/Http/Requests/Admin/CommentsRequest.php (used for validation on update), and the views rendered are in resources/views/admin/comments/*. Tests were ignored per instructions.
